   "description": "Herman Gustav Julius Eländer was a Swedish clergyman and author. He studied in Gothenburg, Kiel, and passed practical theology tests in Linköping. He served as a pastor in Klockrike, Vadstena, and Kisa. He also worked as a preacher at the Östergötland 1st Hospital in Vadstena and was an inspector for Kisa's elementary schools. He authored a few works, including \"Vadstena March\" and wrote on various other topics, as well as travel accounts."
